description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Registered Nurse committed to delivering excellent patient care to join our community nursing team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Community Nursing service has over 200 dedicated professionals who plan and deliver evidence based nursing care to housebound patients within defined localities. You will work both autonomously and collaboratively within supportive teams which comprise of Advanced Clinical Practitioners, &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Community Nurse Team Leaders , Community Nurses, Assistant Practitioners, Nurse Associates , Healthcare Assistants and Administrators as well as with the wider healthcare community.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will need excellent communication and clinical skills and have experience of working within a team; previous community experience is desirable but not essential. You will also be required to use electronic patient record systems, have good time management and be able to prioritise your work load effectively.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Community Nursing teams have implemented a zonal working and named nurse model across the 3 Bristol localities. This change ensures our patients see fewer healthcare professionals and our clinicians cover smaller geographical areas than previously. This also enables greater resilience within teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full and part time hours will be considered .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Weekend and bank holiday working and some late shifts (no nights or out of hours) will be part of this role. You need to have access to a car with a full driving license to apply.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
